Description: Fragment of double handle of a Koan pottery transport amphora to sharpish turn. Clay fine orange-red; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with club symbol.
Curator's comments: Name Zopyros. Trimmed. 325 in Grace/Savvatianou-Petropulaki's unpublished catalogue is a fragmentary stamp from Kos, similar, but not from the same die.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0078)
